Package: murmurfs
Version: 0.1.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.10), python3-pip, fuse
Maintainer: MurmurFS Contributors <murmurfs@example.com>
Description: A FUSE filesystem where AI agents store intent, not content
 MurmurFS lets AI agents write intent summaries instead of full file
 contents. Files are "fuzzy" stacks of intention until synced, at which
 point an LLM synthesizes all layers into concrete files.
 .
 This package includes a Claude/AI understanding guide at
 /usr/share/doc/murmurfs/CLAUDE_GUIDE.md that helps language models
 understand the filesystem design for optimized memory and token usage.
Homepage: https://github.com/ampresent/murmurfs
